        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 12 at 3:40AM EDT by NWS Albany NY</headline>
        <description>At 340 AM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Altamont, or 9 miles southwest of Rotterdam, moving northeast at 10
mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Albany, Schenectady, Rotterdam, Colonie, Scotia, Guilderland,
Niskayuna, Menands, Voorheesville, Altamont, Loudonville, East
Glenville, Knox, Princetown, Shakers, Bleecker Stadium, East Berne,
Gifford, Schonowe, and Helderberg.

This includes the following highways...
Interstate 88 near exit 25.
Interstate 90 between exits 5A and 25a.
Interstate 890 between exits 2A and 9.
Interstate 87 between exits 24 and 4.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
